{{Infobox library | name = Archives Service Center, University Library System, University of Pittsburgh | name_en = <!-- Name in English if different --> | logo = <!-- file name only (no Image: or File:) --> | logo_size = | logo_alt = | image = Archives service center view of building.jpg<!-- file name only (no Image: or File:) --> | image_size = | alt = | caption = | country = United States | type = archives and collections | scope = | established = | ref_legal_mandate = | location = 7500 Thomas Boulevard, Pittsburgh, PA 15208 United States 412-648-3232 | coordinates = {{coord|display=title,inline}} | branch_of = The University of Pittsburgh Library System | num_branches = | items_collected = | collection_size = | criteria = | legal_deposit = | req_to_access = none; handicap accessible, requesting access prior to visiting is recommended; restrictions apply to what can be brought into the reading room | annual_circulation = | pop_served = digital collections are accessible globally; archive contents are open to the public | members = | budget = | director = | num_employees = | website = http://www.library.pitt.edu/archives-service-center | references = | embed = | module = }}
'''Archives Service Center, University Library System, University of Pittsburgh''' ('''ASC''') is one of the main [[Institutional repository|repositories]] within the University Library System at the [[University of Pittsburgh]] and houses collections of various [[manuscript]]s, media, [[map]]s, and other materials of [[history|historical]], social and [[Science|scientific]] content. It houses and functions as the repository for collections that document and describe the history of the Western Pennsylvania region, [[Allegheny County, Pennsylvania]], the city of [[Pittsburgh]], and the University of Pittsburgh.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.library.pitt.edu/archives-service-center|title=Archives Service Center|work=pitt.edu}}</ref>
== Introduction == Some of the history of Pittsburgh and the western Pennsylvania region has been documented by [[primary source]]s on manuscripts, books, maps, personal [[Diary|diaries]], [[audio recording]]s, [[photograph]]s and other materials from the past. The ASC collects material related to the history of this region. The holdings in the collections span over a hundred years, primarily from the mid-19th century to the late 20th century. Some of the content is digitized and accessible online. Content published before 1923 is in the public domain or the rights belong to the University.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.post-gazette.com/local/city/2014/05/23/Historical-documents-put-on-display-here-Group-gets-a-new-look-at-some-very-old-writings/stories/201405230069|title=Manuscript Society gets a new look at some very old writings in Pittsburgh |publisher=Pittsburgh Post-Gazette |last=Sostek |first=Anya |date= 22 May 2014|access-date=27 November 2015 }}</ref><ref>Rare and Special Collections from the Membership of the Association Research Libraries, "Celebrating Research" Association of Association Research Libraries, 21 Dupont Circle NW, Washington, DC 20036</ref> <!--== History == -->
== Major collections == [[File:Pay car Pittsburgh and Lake Erie Railroad Company.JPG|thumb|View of men in line at the pay car of the Pittsburgh and Lake Erie Railroad Company]] Some of ASC's major collections include: {{div col|colwidth=30em}} * Labor<ref>{{cite web|url=http://digital.library.pitt.edu/cgi-bin/f/findaid/findaid-idx?c=ascead&cc=ascead&type=simple&rgn=Category&q1=Labor&Submit=Search|title=Manuscript Collections at the University of Pittsburgh Library System for Labor|publisher=Archives Service Center, University Library System, University of Pittsburgh|date=|access-date= 27 November 2015}}</ref><!--<ref nsmr= Hayes1989/>--><ref>{{cite web | title = Archives Services Center University Library System University of Pittsburgh |publisher=CMU Computer Club |date= | url = http://www.contrib.andrew.cmu.edu/~gm1l/pitt.html|accessdate = 2016-02-23 }}</ref> * University Archives<ref>{{cite web|url=http://pitt.libguides.com/PittUniversityArchives|title=Guide to collections documenting the History of the University of Pittsburgh|publisher=Archives Service Center, University Library System, University of Pittsburgh|date= |access-date= 27 November 2015 }}</ref> * Audio-visual Materials<ref>{{cite web |url= http://pitt.libguides.com/asc-audiovisual |title=Audio and Visual Collections and Holdings |date= 9 October 2015 |publisher=Archives Service Center, University Library System, University of Pittsburgh |access-date= 27 November 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.post-gazette.com/local/city/2015/06/15/Jazz-musician-Erroll-Garner-donates-materials-to-Pitt-library |title=Jazz musician Erroll Garner's materials donated to Pitt library |publisher= Pittsburgh Post-Gazette|last= Niederberger |first=Mary |date=15 June 2015 |access-date=25 November 2015 }}</ref> * Politics and Local Politics<ref>{{cite web|url=http://digital.library.pitt.edu/cgi-bin/f/findaid/findaid-idx?c=ascead&cc=ascead&type=simple&rgn=Category&q1=Politics&Submit=Search|title=Guides to Archives