A '''board mix''' is a recording created by running lines directly off a [[mixing console]] while sound is mixed in real time.<ref name=fearing00>{{cite web |url=http://www.wjffradio.org/FolkPlus/interviews/Fearing.html|title=Stephen Fearing, interviewed 4/9/00 upstairs at Bodles Opera House |accessdate=29 July 2007}}</ref>  The alternative to a board mix is use a [[Mixing console#Virtual Mixing consoles|virtual mixing console]], an increasingly popular approach.

