{{Infobox book | name = Right Here, Right Now: Politics and Leadership in the Age of Disruption | image = | caption = | alt = | author = [[Stephen Harper|Stephen J. Harper]] | title_orig = | orig_lang_code = | title_working = | translator = | illustrator = | cover_artist = | country = Canada | language = English | series = | subject = politics | genre = | published = 2018 (Signal/[[Random House of Canada|Penguin Random House]]) | media_type = Print (hardcover) | pages = 240 | awards = | isbn = 978-0771038624 | oclc = | dewey = | congress = | preceded_by = | followed_by = | wikisource = }} {{Harper sidebar}} '''''Right Here, Right Now: Politics and Leadership in the Age of Disruption''''' is a 2018 non-fiction book by [[Stephen Harper]] concerning the contemporary disruption of economics, politics and society, particularly at a time of populism such as the rise of US President Donald Trump.
==Publication== ''Right Here, Right Now'' was released on 9 October 2018 by the Signal Books imprint of Penguin [[Random House Canada]].<ref>{{cite news | url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2018-10-09/trump-is-a-wake-up-call-for-economic-dogmatists-harper-says | title=Trump Is a Wake-Up Call for Economic Dogmatists, Canada’s Harper Says | date=9 October 2018 | first=Theophilos | last=Argitis | publisher=Bloomberg | accessdate=12 October 2018 }}</ref>
==Reception== Postmedia columnist [[Andrew Coyne]] panned the book, positing various flaws in Harper's portrayal of populism and economics.<ref>{{cite news | url=https://ottawacitizen.com/opinion/andrew-coyne-stephen-harper-reveals-himself-as-banal-in-his-effort-to-claim-mantle-of-populism/wcm/bb42b8b8-b66c-4d46-a759-6993eb7eb91c | title=Coyne: Stephen Harper comes across as banal in effort to claim mantle of populism | date=10 October 2018 | first=Andrew | last=Coyne | newspaper=Ottawa Citizen | accessdate=12 October 2018 }}</ref> ''Toronto Sun'' columnist [[Anthony Furey (writer)|Anthony Furey]]'s positive review declared ''Right Here, Right Now'' to be the "must-read political book of the year".<ref>{{cite news | url=https://torontosun.com/opinion/columnists/stephen-harper-hits-hard-on-carbon-taxes-open-borders-and-more-in-new-book | title=Stephen Harper hits hard on carbon taxes, open borders and more in new book | date=9 October 2018 | first=Anthony | last=Furey | newspaper=Toronto Sun | accessdate=12 October 2018 }}</ref>
